content:
Set Up Service Data in Data Cloud

From the App Launcher, find and open Data Cloud.
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Streams tab and click New.
Select the Salesforce CRM connected data source and click Next.
Select your connected Salesforce org.
Select Data Bundles, then select the Service data bundle, and click Next.
The installed objects and fields are displayed. Don't remove them because Service Intelligence relies on them.
Click Deploy
The Service data bundle deploys 23 data streams.

If you have Knowledge and Einstein Conversation Mining features enabled, deploy additional bundles for ConversationMining and Knowledge to deploy their data streams.

Deploy the Einstein Conversation Mining Insights Data Stream
title: Setting Up Service Data in Salesforce Data Cloud
